The application is missing the X-Content-Type-Options header, which should be used to prevent MIME-type sniffing by browsers. The Content Security Policy (CSP) is improperly configured, as it only defines the frame-ancestors 'self' directive and does not include other essential directives such as default-src, script-src, style-src, and img-src, resulting in an incomplete policy. Additionally, the HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS) header is present but lacks the includeSubDomains and preload directives, indicating a weak configuration. Overall, the application does not enforce a comprehensive set of recommended security headers.
